总统先生
Mr. President--

180
00:10:52,550 --> 00:10:56,510
我觉得  你是自不量力了  布莱斯先生
I think you're in over your head, Mr. Blythe.

181
00:10:56,510 --> 00:10:58,030
容我解释一下
If you would just give me a chance to elaborate--

182
00:10:58,030 --> 00:10:59,230
凭什么让你解释
Why give you a chance?

183
00:10:59,230 --> 00:11:01,800
你对俄罗斯  对中国有什么了解
What do you know about Russia? About China?

184
00:11:01,870 --> 00:11:03,930
我已经听过了...
I've been briefed on--

185
00:11:03,930 --> 00:11:05,320
抱歉  但是
Forgive me, but, uh...

186
00:11:06,210 --> 00:11:07,930
我不愿跟
I don't feel comfortable

187
00:11:07,930 --> 00:11:11,180
总统以外的人进行谈判
negotiating with anyone other than the president.

188
00:11:11,330 --> 00:11:14,510
等他康复  或许我们可以谈谈
When he recovers, perhaps he and I can speak.

189
00:11:16,590 --> 00:11:19,670
我们完事了吗
So, are we finished?

190
00:11:22,580 --> 00:11:24,570
总统情况很糟
The president's in very bad shape.

191
00:11:24,570 --> 00:11:25,600
先生
Sir...

192
00:11:26,030 --> 00:11:27,480
多严重
How serious is it?

193
00:11:33,740 --> 00:11:35,740
他需要肝脏移植
He needs a liver transplant.

194
00:11:37,110 --> 00:11:39,370
我不知道
I wasn't aware that...

195
00:11:41,540 --> 00:11:43,490
你最好习惯跟我磋商
You better get used to negotiating with me.

196
00:11:43,490 --> 00:11:46,890
如果总统死了  那就是你和我
If the president dies, it's you and I...

197
00:11:47,330 --> 00:11:48,600
否则没得可谈
or nothing at all.

198
00:11:50,890 --> 00:11:53,050
抱歉  总统先生
My apologies, Mr. President.

199
00:11:53,050 --> 00:11:56,400
我无意侮辱你
I didn't intend to insult you.

200
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:58,830
我们继续协商  我只求这个
Let's keep a dialogue open. That's all I'm asking.

201
00:11:59,190 --> 00:12:01,960
我想给你一份应对中方要求的
I'd like the opportunity to present you with a detailed proposal

202
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:03,460
具体提议
countering the Chinese demands.

203
00:12:03,460 --> 00:12:06,340
我会让国务卿杜兰特跟你的外交部长接洽
I'll have Secretary Durant work with your foreign minister,

204
00:12:06,340 --> 00:12:07,890
然后我们再谈
and then we'll take it from there.

205
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:10,150
这样可以吗
Are you open to that?

206
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:12,470
当然
Of course.

207
00:12:13,190 --> 00:12:16,840
我很期待看到你的提议
I look forward to reviewing your proposal.

208
00:12:17,190 --> 00:12:18,510
谢谢  总统先生
Thank you, Mr. President.

209
00:12:19,170 --> 00:12:21,620
先生  这消息我们还不希望透露出去
Sir, we didn't want that to get out to the press yet.

210
00:12:21,620 --> 00:12:23,240
美国人民反正也该知道
The American people deserve to know, anyway.

211
00:12:23,240 --> 00:12:25,320
先生  俄罗斯人是见软就欺
Sir, the Russians don't respond well to weakness.

212
00:12:25,320 --> 00:12:26,890
现在他们知道总统...
Now that they know that the president--

213
00:12:26,890 --> 00:12:29,100
你听到他说愿意协商了
You heard him say he's open to negotiation.

214
00:12:29,730 --> 00:12:31,190
我认为这是进展
I'd say that's progress.

215
00:12:43,760 --> 00:12:45,350
四天了  还没有吗
Four days and still nothing?

216
00:12:45,350 --> 00:12:47,250
没有记者招待会  没有通报
No press conference, no briefing.

217
00:12:47,250 --> 00:12:48,130
我们得让他们
We have to let them conduct

218
00:12:48,130 --> 00:12:50,550
按自己的步调进行调查
their investigation on their own terms.

219
00:12:50,610 --> 00:12:52,180
感觉好像我们被蒙在鼓里
Feels like we're being shut out.

220
00:12:52,180 --> 00:12:53,220
不仅仅是联调局
This isn't just the bureau.

221
00:12:53,220 --> 00:12:54,540
他们还得跟国土安全部协调
They have to coordinate with Homeland

222
00:12:54,540 --> 00:12:57,000
-确保敏感...  -扯淡
- and make sure nothing sensitive-- - That's bullshit.

223
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:59,160
古德温有什么情况你不希望我们知道
There's something about Goodwin that you don't want us to know.

224
00:12:59,160 --> 00:13:00,060
不对
Wrong.

225
00:13:00,430 --> 00:13:02,740
我跟你一样想知道他这么做的动机
I wanna know why he did this just as much as you do...

226
00:13:03,040 --> 00:13:05,080
但我们得让联调局做他们的工作
But we've gotta let the FBI do its job.

227
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:20,820
跟我去看他时是同一个论调
Same theory as when I visited him.

228
00:13:21,120 --> 00:13:23,360
那是他达成认罪协议之前  是吗
And that was before he struck the plea, correct?

229
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:25,080
我鼓励他认罪的
I encouraged him to plead guilty.

230
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:27,360
他的宣称毫无依据
His claims were unsubstantiated.

231
00:13:27,360 --> 00:13:28,750
跟我们说说你去见古德温之前
Tell us about your meeting with the president

232
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:30,360
跟总统的见面
prior to that meeting with Goodwin.

233
00:13:30,410 --> 00:13:33,500
卢卡斯拜托我调查  我就调查了
Lucas asked me to investigate. I did.

234
00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:36,000
因此采访了安德伍德
That involved an interview with Underwood.

235
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:37,370
你还留着笔记吗
You still have your notes?

236
00:13:38,510 --> 00:13:40,050
没有搜查令我不会交出笔记
No notes without a warrant.

237
00:13:45,860 --> 00:13:48,460
媒体  没日没夜地打
The press. Calling non-stop.

238
00:13:48,460 --> 00:13:50,210
我们建议调查期间你不要跟任何人...
We suggest you don't speak to anyone while we're still--

239
00:13:50,210 --> 00:13:53,130
别担心  我完全不想被扯进来
Don't worry. I don't have any interest in getting dragged into this.

240
00:13:54,540 --> 00:13:56,250
我去把笔记找出来
Let me go dig up those notes.

241
00:14:29,380 --> 00:14:33,500
布莱斯  他告诉佩特罗夫总统需要移植
Blythe... He told Petrov the president needs a transplant.

242
00:14:34,050 --> 00:14:35,410
他为什么要那么做
Why would he do that?

243
00:14:35,410 --> 00:14:37,000
佩特罗夫把他气到了
Petrov got under his skin.

244
00:14:37,790 --> 00:14:39,740
这就是为什么我们本该按你丈夫的计划来
This is why we should've carried out your husband's plan.

245
00:14:39,740 --> 00:14:41,170
我们给了莫斯科太多操作的空间
We're giving Moscow too much room to maneuver--

246
00:14:41,170 --> 00:14:44,130
我们别谈论无法改变的事了  道格
Let's not debate what we can't change, Doug.

247
00:14:44,790 --> 00:14:47,880
如果莫斯科知道了  我们就得通知媒体
If Moscow knows, we'll have to notify the press.

248
00:14:48,040 --> 00:14:49,610
我们明天就说
We're doing that tomorrow.

249
00:14:49,610 --> 00:14:51,650
由萨克逊医生来做通告
Dr. Saxon will do the briefing.

250
00:14:52,550 --> 00:14:53,670
不  我来吧
No, I'll do it.

251
00:14:53,670 --> 00:14:55,580
还是由第一夫人来说的好
It's better coming from the First Lady.

252
00:14:57,880 --> 00:14:58,920
我同意
I agree.

253
00:15:00,640 --> 00:15:02,340
这事我们也得应对一下
We need to address this, too.

254
00:15:03,530 --> 00:15:05,810
联调局在古德温家找到了他的遗书
The FBI found Goodwin's notes in his house.

255
00:15:07,190 --> 00:15:08,510
可以给处理掉吗
Can we make them disappear?

256
00:15:08,510 --> 00:15:10,950
不行  已经被收为证据了
No, it's already been catalogued.

257
00:15:11,060 --> 00:15:13,360
我们得先一步采取行动控制舆论
We need to get out ahead of it and control the story.

258
00:15:13,950 --> 00:15:17,340
好吧  给我弄一份目前为止的调查报告
All right. Get me a copy and report on the investigation so far.

259
00:15:17,870 --> 00:15:19,050
我想见他
I wanna see him.

260
00:15:20,210 --> 00:15:21,410
总统
The president.

261
00:15:21,520 --> 00:15:23,270
特勤局不许我进去
The Secret Service still won't let me.

262
00:15:23,970 --> 00:15:26,940
请允许斯坦普先生见我丈夫
I'd like Mr. Stamper to have access to my husband, please.

263
00:15:26,940 --> 00:15:28,700
我们有严格命令  夫人  只有您
We have strict orders, ma'am. Only you and--

264
00:15:28,700 --> 00:15:31,070
需要我亲自打给副总统吗
Would you like me to call the vice president myself?

265
00:15:31,560 --> 00:15:33,930
道格拉斯  这位年轻人会送你进去
Douglas, this young man will escort you to his room.

266
00:15:33,930 --> 00:15:34,970
谢谢
Thank you.

267
00:16:59,150 --> 00:17:01,950
-几点了  -7点刚过
- What time is it? - It's a little past 7:00.

268
00:17:11,350 --> 00:17:13,540
先生  先生  是道格
Sir? Sir, it's Doug.

269
00:17:13,690 --> 00:17:14,940
虽然他睁开了眼
Just because his eyes are open

270
00:17:14,940 --> 00:17:16,800
但不代表他的意识完全清醒了
doesn't mean he's fully conscious.

271
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:18,430
肝功能不足
Insufficient liver function.

272
00:17:18,430 --> 00:17:21,520
他的大脑泡在一堆未处理的氨中
His brain is swimming in a pool of unprocessed ammonia.

273
00:17:21,520 --> 00:17:24,580
如果他能看到什么  大概也是严重的幻觉
If he's seeing anything, it's probably severe hallucinations.

274
00:17:24,580 --> 00:17:26,310
他多久能得到肝脏
How long until he has a liver?

275
00:17:26,330 --> 00:17:28,900
可能得要几小时  可能要几天
Could be hours. Could be days.

276
00:17:28,950 --> 00:17:30,600
他是名单上第三位
He's number three on the list.

277
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:31,290
第三名
Number three?

278
00:17:31,290 --> 00:17:33,050
名单按需排序
It's prioritized in terms of need

279
00:17:33,050 --> 00:17:34,980
他是1号情况的第一位
and who was listed first as a Status 1.

280
00:17:34,980 --> 00:17:37,070
他是美国总统啊
He's the President of the United States.

281
00:17:37,070 --> 00:17:38,390
这是法律
It's the law.

282
00:18:13,580 --> 00:18:15,480
司法部长要辞职
The attorney general is resigning.

283
00:18:16,470 --> 00:18:18,790
把这条加入今天下午的新闻发布稿中
Add that to the press release for this afternoon.

284
00:18:20,040 --> 00:18:23,250
-是她的决定还是副总统的  -我的决定
- Uh, her decision or the vice president's? - My decision.

285
00:18:23,250 --> 00:18:25,450
古德温的证人保护计划是司法部的责任
Goodwin's WITSEC was a DOJ responsibility.

286
00:18:25,450 --> 00:18:26,870
我们得找人背锅
We needed a head to roll.

287
00:18:27,510 --> 00:18:28,490
先是她
First hers...

288
00:18:29,530 --> 00:18:30,690
然后你
then yours.

289
00:18:33,100 --> 00:18:34,460
你明天辞职
You'll resign tomorrow.

290
00:18:41,270 --> 00:18:44,640
道格  我知道你现在压力很大  但是
Doug, I know you're under a lot of pressure, but--

291
00:18:44,650 --> 00:18:47,700
是你发了那张南军士兵照片
You sent the photo of the rebel soldier.

292
00:18:48,420 --> 00:18:49,660
不是的
That's not true.

293
00:18:49,770 --> 00:18:52,620
私人手机  没在这里发
Personal phone, off the premises.

294
00:18:53,700 --> 00:18:55,420
可能是有人黑了我的账户什么的
You know, maybe somebody hacked my account or something--

295
00:18:55,420 --> 00:18:57,320
你真要再这么对我撒谎吗
Are you really gonna keep lying to me?

296
00:18:57,510 --> 00:18:59,110
我可以叫人逮捕你
I could have you arrested.

297
00:19:00,530 --> 00:19:02,320
但我宁可你低调离去
But I'd rather you go quietly.

298
00:19:08,530 --> 00:19:09,900
我知道些事  道格
I know things, Doug.

299
00:19:11,690 --> 00:19:13,250
你证明不了什么
Nothing you can prove.

300
00:19:15,150 --> 00:19:16,800
再威胁我啊
Now, threaten me again.

301
00:19:34,410 --> 00:19:36,690
中国如果不加入  提议就没戏
There's no proposal without China's involvement.

302
00:19:36,690 --> 00:19:37,830
凯茜试了
Now, Cathy's tried,

303
00:19:37,830 --> 00:19:41,090
但她跟他们的关系不是特别好
but she doesn't have the best relationship with them.

304
00:19:41,270 --> 00:19:42,930
或许她需要帮助
Maybe she needs some help.

305
00:19:43,680 --> 00:19:44,930
帮助  怎么说
Help? How?

306
00:19:48,850 --> 00:19:50,380
你介意我抽烟吗
Do you mind if I smoke?

307
00:19:50,380 --> 00:19:51,820
当然不
Of course not.

308
00:19:56,390 --> 00:19:58,880
我十年前戒了
I quit about ten years ago.

309
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:01,970
玛乔莉逼我的
Marjory forced me to.

310
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:09,110
还是那么好闻
Ah, still smells delicious.

311
00:20:15,510 --> 00:20:18,000
玛乔莉死时什么样
What was it like when Marjory died?

312
00:20:18,480 --> 00:20:21,870
那是...
Oh, well, it was, um...

313
00:20:22,840 --> 00:20:25,080
抱歉  如果你不愿意我们不用谈这个
I'm sorry. We don't have to talk about it if you don't want.

314
00:20:25,080 --> 00:20:26,390
不  没事
No, it's fine.

315
00:20:27,440 --> 00:20:30,330
我们当时已经数月没有真正聊过了
We hadn't had a real conversation in... in months.

316
00:20:30,330 --> 00:20:31,700
她的神智已经不清楚了
Her mind was gone.

317
00:20:32,960 --> 00:20:34,780
她最终死时
When she finally died,

318
00:20:35,160 --> 00:20:38,940
感觉好像被砍掉根肋骨
it felt like a limb had been hacked off.

319
00:20:39,680 --> 00:20:42,430
我...痛不欲生
I felt... devastated.

320
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:47,470
但也如释重负
But I also felt relieved.

321
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:53,080
我对我母亲的感觉就是这样
That's what I feel about my mother.

322
00:20:54,490 --> 00:20:56,760
我不...我都没想起来
Oh, I hadn't-- It hadn't even occurred to me.

323
00:20:56,760 --> 00:20:58,720
除了弗兰克  你母亲也病了
You have Frank and your mother.

324
00:21:00,480 --> 00:21:02,070
父亲去世时  我几乎崩溃了
When my father died, it destroyed me,

325
00:21:02,070 --> 00:21:05,490
但想到我母亲时  我毫无感觉
but when I think about Mother, I feel nothing.

326
00:21:05,760 --> 00:21:08,090
-你们不亲近吗  -不
- You two aren't close? - No.

327
00:21:11,950 --> 00:21:14,660
我对弗兰西斯也是这种感觉
And I feel the same about Francis.

328
00:21:14,740 --> 00:21:15,880
毫无感觉
Nothing.

329
00:21:20,610 --> 00:21:22,460
我知道这听起来很可怕
I know that must sound awful.

330
00:21:24,150 --> 00:21:25,760
这很难接受
It's a lot to process.

331
00:21:27,520 --> 00:21:30,050
这没有正误之分
There's no right way or wrong way.

332
00:21:35,190 --> 00:21:37,160
-等下  慢着  -不
- Wait, hold on. - No.

333
00:21:37,690 --> 00:21:39,420
玛乔莉不会同意的
Marjory wouldn't approve.

334
00:21:40,240 --> 00:21:41,970
刚刚说到哪了
We got sidetracked.

335
00:21:42,130 --> 00:21:44,400
对  中国
Yes. China.

336
00:21:45,180 --> 00:21:48,860
我有个主意  如果你相信我能做好的话
I have an idea, if you can trust me to handle it.

337
00:21:49,070 --> 00:21:52,030
我赌上命相信你  克莱尔
I'd trust you with my goddamn life, Claire.

338
00:21:53,470 --> 00:21:54,210
怎么样
Comment c'est elle?

339
00:21:55,230 --> 00:21:56,510
你不会想知道的
You don't want to know.

340
00:22:01,330 --> 00:22:02,200
喝点水吧
Water?

341
00:22:03,350 --> 00:22:05,190
不用  妈妈
Non, ca va, mamon.

342
00:22:05,520 --> 00:22:08,270
我可不希望你们中暑了
Je veux pas vous laisse attraper un coup de chaleur, vous voyez?

343
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:12,880
我来拿  谢谢
I got it. Ah, merci.

344
00:22:20,800 --> 00:22:21,880
这是谁
C'est qui?

345
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:25,390
没谁  同事而已
Non, c'est un colleague de moi.

346
00:22:25,790 --> 00:22:26,410
给你  妈妈
Mamon.

347
00:22:29,150 --> 00:22:30,090
莉安
LeAnn.

348
00:22:30,730 --> 00:22:32,910
找你可真难
You are a tough guy to track down.

349
00:22:33,390 --> 00:22:36,080
-你来干什么  -你要赶飞机
- What are you doing here? - You have a plane to catch.

350
00:22:36,630 --> 00:22:38,080
第一夫人需要你的帮助
The First Lady needs your help.

351
00:22:38,150 --> 00:22:39,880
我不想和他们有任何瓜葛
I don't want to have anything to do with them.

352
00:22:39,880 --> 00:22:41,210
无论你对总统的看法如何
Whatever you think of the president,

353
00:22:41,210 --> 00:22:43,120
你对祖国依然负有责任
you still have a duty to your country.

354
00:22:43,230 --> 00:22:45,540
就算他在我离开白宫的那天去世
Even if he dies, the day I walked out the White House,

355
00:22:45,540 --> 00:22:47,550
我也向自己承诺过不会回去
I promised myself I wasn't going back.

356
00:22:47,550 --> 00:22:49,370
你连我们的计划都不知道
You don't even know what we have in mind.

357
00:22:49,560 --> 00:22:52,350
无所谓  我不去
It doesn't matter. I'm not going.

358
00:22:52,540 --> 00:22:53,880
我想请你离开
I'd like you to leave.

359
00:22:56,950 --> 00:22:58,580
这是基本情况的材料
Here's your briefing materials.

360
00:22:58,580 --> 00:22:59,420
你没听见我说吗
You're not hearing me.

361
00:22:59,430 --> 00:23:00,980
你真应该看一眼
You should really take a look.

362
00:23:15,120 --> 00:23:17,070
她的竞选会完蛋的
Her campaign would be over.

