00:31:57,810 --> 00:31:59,370
我那是在自欺欺人
I was fooling myself.

539
00:32:00,970 --> 00:32:03,390
总统刚被枪击
So, president gets shot,

540
00:32:03,870 --> 00:32:07,500
你就忍不住要趁火打劫了
and you just can't help taking advantage of the chaos.

541
00:32:09,250 --> 00:32:11,970
你所说的火  我称之为机遇
What you call chaos, I call opportunity.

542
00:32:14,630 --> 00:32:16,150
你是我的第一位客户
And you're my first client.

543
00:32:20,500 --> 00:32:22,270
祝你好运
I wish you the best.

544
00:32:23,470 --> 00:32:25,680
但我不是你的第一位客户
But I'm not your first client.

545
00:32:26,610 --> 00:32:28,850
我不想跟白宫扯上关系
I don't wanna have anything to do with the White House.

546
00:32:28,850 --> 00:32:31,220
你因为沃克的丑闻损失了很多钱
You lost a lot of money during the Walker scandal.

547
00:32:32,810 --> 00:32:36,450
没错  正因此我才要拒绝你
I did, indeed, which is why I'm turning you down.

548
00:32:37,590 --> 00:32:40,300
我很抱歉你跑了这么大老远结果被拒绝
I'm sorry you came all the way out here for a "No."

549
00:32:49,070 --> 00:32:50,820
你不想进监狱吧
You don't wanna go to prison, do you?

550
00:32:52,800 --> 00:32:54,140
再失去仅剩的一切
Lose the rest of it?

551
00:32:54,140 --> 00:32:55,710
我已经被赦免了
I've already been pardoned.

552
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:01,040
免的是洗钱罪  不是伪证罪
For the money laundering, not for perjury.

553
00:33:03,250 --> 00:33:04,690
你说沃克知道  但是他不知道
You said that Walker knew, and he didn't.

554
00:33:04,690 --> 00:33:07,860
你没有说你当时在跟弗兰克合作
What you didn't say is that you were working with Frank.

555
00:33:10,600 --> 00:33:12,900
人家凭什么相信你而不是我
Why should anybody believe you more than me?

556
00:33:13,050 --> 00:33:14,540
你要么赌一把
You take that chance...

557
00:33:14,870 --> 00:33:17,260
然后看着克雷顿-维斯特变成低价股
and watch Clayton West become a penny stock.

558
00:33:18,360 --> 00:33:21,700
要么我们成为终结石油危机的英雄
Or we're heroes for ending the oil crisis,

559
00:33:21,700 --> 00:33:24,600
大家都发财  你也能重树形象
everybody gets rich, your image is restored.

560
00:33:26,820 --> 00:33:28,210
他们也许还会让你选
They'll probably even let you choose

561
00:33:28,210 --> 00:33:30,350
下一任驻北京的大使
the next ambassador in Beijing.

562
00:33:37,430 --> 00:33:39,610
你并不认为那有一丝真实性
So you don't think any of it is true?

563
00:33:39,670 --> 00:33:40,630
不
No.

564
00:33:41,280 --> 00:33:43,230
我也想相信他
And I wanted to believe him.

565
00:33:44,750 --> 00:33:47,120
那第一夫人泪眼汪汪说的那些话
So the First Lady's whole teary-eyed thing?

566
00:33:47,950 --> 00:33:49,740
我觉得她是对的
I think she's right.

567
00:33:49,740 --> 00:33:51,700
卢卡斯是哪里崩溃了吧
Something in Lucas snapped.

568
00:33:52,640 --> 00:33:55,610
我认识的卢卡斯不会想杀死总统
I mean, the Lucas I knew wouldn't have tried to kill a president.

569
00:33:55,610 --> 00:33:58,140
没错  我就是这意思
Exactly. That's my point.

570
00:33:58,640 --> 00:34:02,230
你真觉得安德伍德杀过人吗
You honestly think Underwood was murdering people?

571
00:34:02,230 --> 00:34:03,720
你的怀疑态度哪去了
Where is your skepticism?

572
00:34:03,720 --> 00:34:07,120
我怀疑卢卡斯  也怀疑白宫
I'm skeptical of Lucas and I'm skeptical of the White House.

573
00:34:07,130 --> 00:34:08,560
那怎么没证据
How come there's no proof?

574
00:34:08,970 --> 00:34:10,140
一点没有
None.

575
00:34:10,290 --> 00:34:13,380
卢卡斯试了  我也试了
After Lucas tried, after I tried.

576
00:34:15,040 --> 00:34:16,670
我的建议是算了吧
My advice is to let it go.

577
00:34:17,450 --> 00:34:20,260
你只会重复我们的徒劳
You're gonna repeat the same goose chase we did.

578
00:34:21,090 --> 00:34:22,380
我总得问一下
I had to ask.

579
00:34:24,420 --> 00:34:26,510
-你的编辑怎么说  -说算了吧
- What does your editor say? - To let it go.

580
00:34:26,510 --> 00:34:27,660
你看吧
You see?

581
00:34:27,980 --> 00:34:30,790
-他可不如你  -那是我以前
- He's not as good as you are. - Was.

582
00:34:31,890 --> 00:34:33,630
真希望你在《电讯报》工作
Wish you were at The Telegraph.

583
00:34:34,380 --> 00:34:36,250
是啊  要是有人被开了就告诉我
Yeah, let me know if anyone gets fired.

584
00:34:45,080 --> 00:34:46,270
门没关
It's open.

585
00:34:52,880 --> 00:34:54,490
我一收到你的短信就尽快赶过来了
I came as soon as I got your text.

586
00:34:54,490 --> 00:34:56,370
发布会后我们忙得不可开交
We've been slammed since the press conference.

587
00:34:56,610 --> 00:34:57,850
情况怎么样
How's it lookin'?

588
00:34:57,850 --> 00:34:59,800
邓巴的事大受关注
Major play on the Dunbar story.

589
00:35:01,320 --> 00:35:03,640
让第一夫人去说是个好主意
It was a good idea to have the First Lady talk.

590
00:35:04,700 --> 00:35:05,820
你要喝苏打水吗
You want a soda?

591
00:35:06,010 --> 00:35:07,380
来杯水什么的吗
A glass of water or anything?

592
00:35:08,720 --> 00:35:09,980
水就好
Water's fine.

593
00:35:19,460 --> 00:35:21,070
我已决定让你留下了
I've decided you can stay.

594
00:35:22,480 --> 00:35:24,540
道格  我希望你能理解
Doug, I hope you can understand.

595
00:35:25,790 --> 00:35:27,130
我紧张了
I got nervous.

596
00:35:27,580 --> 00:35:29,510
当时情况看起来不太好
You know, things weren't looking good and...

597
00:35:30,380 --> 00:35:33,250
我想留条退路  以防万一
yeah, I wanted an out, in case I needed one.

598
00:35:33,490 --> 00:35:35,340
那的确是个错误  我希望我没有那样做
I mean, it was a mistake. I wish I hadn't.

599
00:35:35,340 --> 00:35:36,560
你纠正了你的错误
You corrected your mistakes.

600
00:35:36,560 --> 00:35:38,710
那才是最重要的  要冰块吗
That's all that matters. You want ice?

601
00:35:38,710 --> 00:35:39,790
好的
Sure.

602
00:35:49,210 --> 00:35:51,850
我们现在不能让竞选再出现问题了
We can't afford any more shake-ups in the campaign right now,

603
00:35:51,850 --> 00:35:53,730
尤其总统还在医院里
especially with the president in the hospital.

604
00:35:55,500 --> 00:35:57,780
我们也不能让你再犯错
We also can't afford any more of your mistakes.

605
00:36:01,920 --> 00:36:04,930
闭嘴  闭嘴
Shut up. Shut up!

606
00:36:05,700 --> 00:36:08,220
我刚醒来的时候  说不出话
When I first woke up, I couldn't speak.

607
00:36:08,220 --> 00:36:10,160
我得眨眼来表达我的反应
I had to blink my eyes if I wanted to respond.

608
00:36:10,160 --> 00:36:11,380
你明白吗
Do you understand?

609
00:36:13,380 --> 00:36:15,600
如果我得不到你的忠诚
If I can't get your loyalty,

610
00:36:16,270 --> 00:36:18,240
那我就要你顺从
I will have your obedience.

611
00:36:18,540 --> 00:36:19,600
眨眼
Blink.

612
00:36:21,190 --> 00:36:22,180
眨眼
Blink!

613
00:36:26,520 --> 00:36:27,550
该死
Fuck!

614
00:36:39,240 --> 00:36:40,170
该死的
Fucking...

615
00:36:47,720 --> 00:36:48,730
给
Here.

616
00:36:49,850 --> 00:36:51,290
你有病  伙计
You're fucked up, man.

617
00:37:10,530 --> 00:37:12,430
-别叫了  -早上好  汉默施密特先生
- Quit it. - Good morning, Mr. Hammerschmidt.

618
00:37:12,430 --> 00:37:13,280
有什么事吗
How can I help you?

619
00:37:13,280 --> 00:37:14,740
我们来还你的笔记
Uh, we're just returning your notes.

620
00:37:14,750 --> 00:37:17,190
我们复印过了  这是原件
We made copies. These are the originals.

621
00:37:17,190 --> 00:37:18,580
不是很有用吧
Nothing too useful, huh?

622
00:37:18,590 --> 00:37:20,800
是的  先生  但还是感谢你的配合
No, sir, but thank you for your cooperation.

623
00:37:20,800 --> 00:37:22,980
还有你的报纸  放在台阶上的
Your paper, too. It was on the step.

624
00:37:23,360 --> 00:37:24,680
祝你今天愉快  汉默施密特先生
Well, you have a good day, Mr. Hammerschmidt.

625
00:37:24,680 --> 00:37:25,790
你们也是
You, too.

626
00:37:33,690 --> 00:37:35,080
不要告诉我你又饿了
Don't tell me you're hungry already.

627
00:37:35,080 --> 00:37:37,470
我才喂过你  天呐
I just fed you. Good God.

628
00:37:37,470 --> 00:37:40,170
来了  来了  来了  来了
I'm coming. I'm coming, I'm coming, I'm coming.

629
00:38:16,100 --> 00:38:18,580
-早上好  -早上好
- Morning. - Morning.

630
00:38:24,900 --> 00:38:27,470
我建议让凯茜来做谈判
I suggest we turn the negotiations over to Cathy.

631
00:38:27,700 --> 00:38:29,650
如果我们一直拖着俄罗斯  油价会
If we keep stalling on Russia, gas prices will--

632
00:38:29,660 --> 00:38:31,010
现在不是说这个的时候
Now is not a good time.

633
00:38:32,330 --> 00:38:33,140
我不会让总统
I won't have the president

634
00:38:33,140 --> 00:38:34,860
回到一个一片混乱的白宫
come back to a White House in disarray.

635
00:38:34,860 --> 00:38:36,620
我们不知道他会不会回来
We don't know that he is coming back.

636
00:38:37,360 --> 00:38:40,560
他会的  我向你保证
He is. I promise you that.

637
00:38:41,130 --> 00:38:44,370
你是上帝吗  你有什么资格保证
Are you God? Who are you to say?

638
00:38:45,600 --> 00:38:46,240
什么事
Yes?

639
00:38:46,240 --> 00:38:48,460
塔斯克先生和丹顿先生来了
Mr. Tusk and Mr. Danton are here.

640
00:38:48,460 --> 00:38:49,580
让他们进来
Send them in.

641
00:38:49,720 --> 00:38:52,110
今早安排的  我们要讨论俄罗斯的事
It was arranged this morning. We're discussing Russia.

642
00:38:52,150 --> 00:38:53,690
先生  我是幕僚长
Sir, I am the Chief of Staff.

643
00:38:53,690 --> 00:38:55,460
这些事情你必须让我知道
You have to keep me informed of these things.

644
00:38:55,460 --> 00:38:56,490
不好意思
Excuse me,

645
00:38:56,490 --> 00:38:58,130
但我觉得应该是你要听我的
but I believe you answer to me,

646
00:38:58,130 --> 00:38:59,380
而不是反过来
not the other way around.

647
00:38:59,380 --> 00:39:01,050
国务卿杜兰特应该参加这个会
Secretary Durant should be here.

648
00:39:01,050 --> 00:39:02,160
这是一次私下碰面
This meeting is private.

649
00:39:02,160 --> 00:39:03,590
我之后会跟你们俩讨论
I'll discuss it with you both after.

650
00:39:03,590 --> 00:39:05,470
总统绝不会允许雷蒙德
The president would never allow Raymond--

651
00:39:06,550 --> 00:39:08,770
-总统先生  -塔斯克先生
- Mr. President. - Mr. Tusk.

652
00:39:10,150 --> 00:39:11,210
雷米  很高兴见到你
Remy, good to see you.

653
00:39:11,210 --> 00:39:13,380
-总统先生  -斯坦普先生
- Mr. President. - Mr. Stamper.

654
00:39:15,170 --> 00:39:16,980
我们稍后继续  道格
I'll follow up with you later, Doug.

655
00:39:17,040 --> 00:39:18,230
是  先生
Yes, sir.

656
00:39:19,410 --> 00:39:21,270
感谢您这么快就抽出时间见我们
Thanks for taking the time to meet with us on such short notice.

657
00:39:21,280 --> 00:39:23,920
石油的问题没时间可以浪费了
Well, there's no time to waste on this oil thing.

658
00:39:24,040 --> 00:39:26,460
我跟中国那边有了些进展
I've made some progress with the Chinese.

659
00:39:26,880 --> 00:39:28,450
先生  第一夫人现在在里面
Sir, the First Lady is in there right now.

660
00:39:28,450 --> 00:39:29,920
她在等我
She's expecting me.

661
00:39:36,720 --> 00:39:37,830
我们还想赢得选举呢
We're trying to win an election,

662
00:39:37,830 --> 00:39:38,850
你却想提醒所有人
and you want to remind everyone

663
00:39:38,860 --> 00:39:40,880
总统赦免了雷蒙德·塔斯克
that the president pardoned Raymond Tusk?

664
00:39:40,880 --> 00:39:42,520
我们换个地方说
Let's find somewhere else.

665
00:39:42,520 --> 00:39:44,130
这都是国家大事
These are matters of state.

666
00:39:44,210 --> 00:39:46,260
你无权干涉
You don't have the authority to intervene.

667
00:39:46,720 --> 00:39:49,160
如果唐纳德想听我的建议  那他就有权这么做
If Donald wants my counsel, that is his prerogative.

668
00:39:49,160 --> 00:39:50,740
你故意骗我
You are deliberately deceiving me.

669
00:39:50,740 --> 00:39:53,750
-你背着我  -你忘了你的身份  道格拉斯
- Going behind my-- - You have forgotten your place, Douglas.

670
00:39:53,770 --> 00:39:56,950
我的身份  那你呢
My place? What about your place?

671
00:39:57,300 --> 00:39:59,190
你在他最需要你时离开  还威胁他
You leave him when he needs you most, you threaten him,

672
00:39:59,190 --> 00:40:01,410
现在他进了医院  你还拆他的台
and now that he's in here, you undermine him.

673
00:40:01,410 --> 00:40:03,420
-你应该  -别说了  够了
- You're supposed to be-- - Stop. That is enough.

674
00:40:03,920 --> 00:40:05,600
我会告诉你一切
I will fill you in on everything,

675
00:40:05,600 --> 00:40:07,640
但不是在这儿  而是在白宫
but not here. At the White House.

676
00:40:10,310 --> 00:40:11,340
怎么了
What's happening?

677
00:40:11,710 --> 00:40:12,760
他的心脏
His heart.

678
00:40:14,040 --> 00:40:17,070
-医生  -他有些偶发心律不齐
- Doctor? - He's had some sporadic arrhythmia.

679
00:40:17,070 --> 00:40:19,300
-请出去一下好吗  -好
- Will you give us the room for a moment? - Of course.

680
00:40:25,930 --> 00:40:27,480
我们不能一直斗下去
We can't keep battling each other,

681
00:40:27,490 --> 00:40:29,090
他都这样子了
not with him like this.

682
00:40:29,470 --> 00:40:30,650
我们需要一条新的道路
We need a new path forward,

683
00:40:30,650 --> 00:40:32,560
我希望你能帮忙
and I would like your help with that.

684
00:40:32,700 --> 00:40:35,620
我保证不会瞒着你
I promise I won't keep you in the dark.

685
00:40:37,160 --> 00:40:39,640
等你准备好  我们白宫见
I'll meet you at the White House whenever you're ready.

686
00:40:39,910 --> 00:40:43,410
我要留在这里  我觉得这更重要
I'm staying here. I think this is more important.

687
00:40:44,890 --> 00:40:45,990
好
Okay.

688
00:40:57,850 --> 00:40:59,030
安德伍德夫人
Mrs. Underwood.

689
00:40:59,650 --> 00:41:02,700
关于如何对付俄罗斯
Mr. Tusk and Mr. Danton have a proposal

690
00:41:02,700 --> 00:41:04,390
塔斯克先生和丹顿先生有个提议
about how to deal with Russia.

691
00:41:05,150 --> 00:41:08,440
您今天最没想到会见到的就是我吧
I imagine I'm the last person you expected to see today.

692
00:41:09,560 --> 00:41:10,670
见到你们二位
I am a bit surprised,

693
00:41:10,670 --> 00:41:12,760
我的确有些惊讶
yes, to see both of you.

694
00:41:13,240 --> 00:41:15,480
大家对我们的到来肯定都有些警觉
I'm sure there's some wariness about us being here,

695
00:41:15,480 --> 00:41:19,240
但我们有个对付俄罗斯的好计划
but I think we have a good plan on how to handle Russia.

696
00:41:19,910 --> 00:41:21,080
你想加入吗
Would you like to join us?

697
00:41:21,080 --> 00:41:23,010
让雷蒙德给你详说
Raymond can lay it out for you.

698
00:41:23,290 --> 00:41:25,480
我不知道我能提供些什么
Well, I don't know what I can offer.

699
00:41:25,840 --> 00:41:28,600
要是我又开始跟白宫合作的消息传出去
Well, we're going to catch some flack if word gets out

700
00:41:28,600 --> 00:41:30,620
我们肯定要受到抨击的
that I'm back in business with the White House.

701
00:41:30,620 --> 00:41:32,910
你可以帮我们平息那些声音
You could help us smooth that over.

702
00:41:32,910 --> 00:41:36,530
你的新闻发布会相当感人
Your press conference was very moving.

703
00:41:38,250 --> 00:41:40,780
-弗兰克的事  我很遗憾  -谢谢
- I'm sorry about Frank. - Thank you.

704
00:41:41,060 --> 00:41:42,640
当然  他要是知道我进了总统办公室
Of course, he'd have a conniption fit

705
00:41:42,640 --> 00:41:45,170
肯定会大发脾气
if he knew I were in the Oval Office.

706
00:41:47,680 --> 00:41:50,510
他是个实用主义者  雷蒙德  只要成功就行
Well, he is a pragmatist, Raymond. Whatever works.

707
00:41:50,820 --> 00:41:53,260
-我们继续吧  -雷米
- Shall we continue? - Remy.

708
00:41:53,610 --> 00:41:55,730
计划是提出建立
So, the plan is to propose a partnership

709
00:41:55,730 --> 00:41:58,800
美中能源公司合作伙伴关系
between American and Chinese energy companies.

710
00:42:25,020 --> 00:42:27,010
你有点紧张
You seem nervous.

711
00:42:27,440 --> 00:42:28,670
有一阵子没见了
It's been a while.

712
00:42:54,950 --> 00:42:56,390
我该怎么办  老大
What should I do, boss?

713
00:43:20,650 --> 00:43:21,580
萨克逊医生
Dr. Saxon.

714
00:43:27,470 --> 00:43:28,930
我想捐肝
I'd like to donate.

715
00:43:29,730 --> 00:43:31,710
-斯坦普先生  -我是O型血
- Mr. Stamper-- - My blood type is O.

716
00:43:32,040 --> 00:43:33,930
我很健康  我们开始做测试吧
I'm healthy. Let's do the tests.

717
00:43:34,190 --> 00:43:36,690
健康不是捐肝的唯一标准
